Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on data loss prevention and protection against malware attacks. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper proposes a new solution for protecting user data. 
- cs.OS (Operating Systems) is relevant as the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed solution on different operating systems. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper involves the use of Trusted Execution Environments (TEEs) and discusses the impact on system performance.
